title: Rutgers football vs. Ohio State scouting report
text:
MORE Rutgers Football Scouting Report
Who: No. 1 Ohio State (7-0, 3-0) at Rutgers (3-3, 1-2)
Where: High Point Solutions Stadium/Piscataway.
When: 8 p.m.
TV: ABC.
Radio: WNYM 970-AM, WCTC 1450-AM, WENJ 97.3-FM, WTMR 800-AM.
Series: Ohio State leads 1-0.
3 KEYS
1. Ohio State quarterbacks. J.T. Barrett, the 2014 Big Ten Offensive Player of the Year, will make his first start of the season after supplanting Cardale Jones. Remember, Jones, who led Ohio State to the national title after Barrett was injured near the end of last season, edged Barrett for the starting job during the preseason and is 10-0 in his career as starter. Coach Urban Meyer said Jones will have an active role in the game but didn’t specify. Rutgers typically fairs better against mobile quarterbacks like Barrett than pocket-passers like Jones, but had no answers for Barrett in last season’s 56-17 loss.
